                            <comment id="472321" author="arshad512" created="Sat, 20 Sep 2025 17:43:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 Master : &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/815e3ac0-bd5d-455e-9153-eaa8357b1a48&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/815e3ac0-bd5d-455e-9153-eaa8357b1a48&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="465650" author="nangelinas" created="Thu, 31 Jul 2025 10:40:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on master: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/91b22842-8d90-4ca8-968e-865411ea8bc5&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/91b22842-8d90-4ca8-968e-865411ea8bc5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="461186" author="JIRAUSER18717" created="Wed, 25 Jun 2025 09:36:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on recent master at &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/cb3cf585-ffe8-4422-b7b9-ffd4edd772f1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/cb3cf585-ffe8-4422-b7b9-ffd4edd772f1&lt;/a&gt; .&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Trying to understand what&apos;s going wrong by digging into to the test-set logs, I have found that when the timeout is being triggered, at least one of the VMs involved during the failing sub-test, as a Server or a Client, is complaining with LNet/NFS timeout messages.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And I have verified that this is also the case at &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/240b8af2-3c16-4987-b7b1-a287dd179e8d&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/240b8af2-3c16-4987-b7b1-a287dd179e8d&lt;/a&gt; that has been the reason of this ticket creation !&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So my guess is that this is only a new symptom/consequence of the same networking issue inside the auto-test infrastructure, already being pointed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18569&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;LU-18569&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18693&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;LU-18693&lt;/a&gt; , ....&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
